    Folder Structures:


            test->java->base
                      ->config
                      ->models
                      ->services
                      ->specs
                      ->support
                      ->tests
                 ->resources
                    ->schemas


base     -> BaseTest.java file (this file tests the url and env is accesable or not)

config   -> ConfigReader ( Reads The Environment variables)
         -> DatabaseConfig ( Configures the database to do database testing)

models  -> OrderRequest(tells what to include in order request)
        -> OrderResponse(tells what will the api responses as a order response)
        -> OrderRow(What all the columns does order contain)

services -> AuthService ( provide authentication service so that it is used in tests)
         -> OrderService(provide full order flow service)

specs    -> RequestSpecs (contains all the specs used for request its like a factory)
         -> ResponseSpecs (Contains all the response specs later to be used in tests)

support  -> DbSupport (Contains all the required database operations)
         -> TestEnvironment(read the env file)
         -> TokenManager(returns the token from AuthService)

tests    -> AuthenticationTest ( tests the user is authored or not ) -- test passed
         -> DatabaseConnectionTest ( Database is connected ) -- test passed
         -> DatabaseValidationTest( The connected database is reachable or not ) -- test passed
         -> NegativeTests( Failure Path if the user is not authorised ,not validated ,wrong password or wrong username) -- test passed
         -> OrderDbValidationTest( Created order is storing in db or not ) -- test passed
         -> OrderLifecycleTest(full order lifecycle from start to end created->allocated-shipped) -- test passed
         -> ProductXmlSchemaTest(prodcut is matching the schema or not) -- test passed
         -> TestContainerSmokeTest(uses the test container) -- test failed

schemas -> allocate-schema.json (schema for order allocation)
        -> create-order-schema.json (schema for order creation)
        -> error-schema.json (schema for any errors)
        -> order-schema.json (schema for order)
        -> ship-schema.json ( schema for shipment details)
        -> product.xsd ( product schema in xsd format)



